        "id": 5185
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-01-27T23:17:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t really intend this as an Android feature.  They do have the option to pretend Alpha8 is Gray8 when they decode, but I don\u0027t see a reason to add that as an encoding feature.  I think our other encoders also fail on Alpha8 input.\n\nIt is nice to support Gray as a general Skia feature, since it makes perfect sense to encode Gray jpgs.",
      "revId": "5cb4bc3333afc2b7875b6133d84cf3f548b01478",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
