        "id": 5185
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-01-27T00:48:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I would really like to disable jpeg encodes if the input is not opaque.  I\u0027m guessing that would break Android (and other clients?).\n\nIf not that, I would really like to unpremultiply before encoding (so we at least encode premul/unpremul images the same), but I\u0027m guessing this would change Android behavior.\n\nSo now I\u0027m adding F16 and it behaves just like RGBA/BGRA, the alpha type and alpha channel are ignored.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 32,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 32,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "5cb4bc3333afc2b7875b6133d84cf3f548b01478",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ba1e39ba_ed1ec263",
        "filename": "src/images/SkJPEGImageEncoder.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 32,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-01-27T15:08:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I would really like to disable jpeg encodes if the input is not opaque. \n\nThis is something we\u0027ve actually thought about before. See crrev.com/1517523003 and skbug.com/1501\n\n\u003e I\u0027m guessing that would break Android (and other clients?).\n\nThe Android case might be easy to fix, since we can update the calling code.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e If not that, I would really like to unpremultiply before encoding (so we at least encode premul/unpremul images the same),\n\u003e but I\u0027m guessing this would change Android behavior.\n\nThis was the motivation for the above bug. The client wanted to encode as a JPEG (for PDF), but if there is alpha, they want to unpremultiply and store the alpha in a separate transparency mask. Hal, since you own PDF now, what are your thoughts?\n\n\u003e \n\u003e So now I\u0027m adding F16 and it behaves just like RGBA/BGRA, the alpha type and alpha channel are ignored.\n\nMaybe add a TODO with a reference to the old bug, if you think it\u0027s worth considering? (Or if we again decide it\u0027s not, a reminder of why we made the decision?)",
      "revId": "5cb4bc3333afc2b7875b6133d84cf3f548b01478",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
