      "message": "We may remove the color space or return false due to its absence, but the only time we ever look at the color space is if the color type is F16. Does F16 support legacy behavior? (Looking deeper, I realize that if we removed the color space from an F16 input due to using the legacy premul behavior, we would return false from choose_proc.)",
